FBIS4-67212 "jptdd021__l94065" JPRS-TDD-94-021-L JPRS Narcotics 12 May 1994 EAST EUROPE BULGARIA More Than 120 Kg of Heroin Seized at Danube Bridge Checkpoint More Than 120 Kg of Heroin Seized at Danube Bridge Checkpoint AU1205161894 Sofia BTA in English 1533 GMT 12 May 94 AU1205161894 Sofia BTA English BFN [Text] Ruse, May 12 (BTA) -- More than 120 kg of heroin--refined, according to police sources, and unrefined, according to the prosecuting magistracy--have been seized at the Danube Bridge checkpoint in Ruse. The narcotic was distributed in about 250 packets and concealed under the bed on top the driver's cabin of a Fiat caravan which was leaving Bulgaria. The boy and the girl--both from Germany--travelling in the Fiat were arrested. This is the largest amount of heroin discovered at the Danube Bridge checkpoint so far.
